# Core Pi docs (this playground)

You are editing one of **`docs/TOOLS.md`**, **`docs/SKILLS.md`**, **`docs/AGENTS.md`**, or **`docs/AGENT_TEAMS.md`**.

## Keep consistent

1. **Terminology** — Use the same distinctions as **[docs/CONCEPTS.md](docs/CONCEPTS.md)** (tools vs extensions vs agents vs skills). Do not describe skills as “registering tools” or agents as “extensions.”
2. **Cross-links** — When you add a section that overlaps another guide, link to it (e.g. TOOLS ↔ EXTENSIONS `registerTool`; AGENTS ↔ AGENT_TEAMS for `teams.yaml` / presets; SKILLS ↔ upstream `skills.md` / **REPO_INDEX** for paths).
3. **Paths** — Project layout and **`extensions/`** vs **`.pi/extensions/`** shims: **[docs/EXTENSIONS.md](docs/EXTENSIONS.md)** and **[docs/REPO_INDEX.md](docs/REPO_INDEX.md)**.
4. **Repo truth** — If you document behavior (e.g. `dispatch_agent`, team tools), verify against **`extensions/agent-team.ts`** (or the relevant extension) so the markdown matches the code.
5. **Index** — After substantive additions, update **[docs/README.md](docs/README.md)** if a new major section deserves a one-line table row.

## Quick map

| File | Primary topic |
|------|----------------|
| **TOOLS.md** | Built-ins, extension tools, agent `tools:` allowlists |
